cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE, cs.AI 

This paper is about speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses training processes for LSTM networks, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes alternative deep LSTM architectures, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
